title: Queen Liliuokalani Day
context: [§8-5.5] Queen Liliuokalani Day. September 2 of each year shall be known and recognized as &ldquo;Queen Liliuokalani Day&rdquo; in memory of the birth of Queen Liliuokalani on September 2, 1838; provided that this day shall not be a state holiday. [L 1993, c 11, §1]
